The article is a statement made by the President on the 17th anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda. The President reflects on the unimaginable slaughter that took place in Rwanda, resulting in the deaths of over 800,000 innocent people. He pays tribute to the memory of those lost and emphasizes the importance of learning from this tragic chapter in history. The President acknowledges the capacity for both evil and good in humanity, highlighting the courageous Rwandans who risked their lives to save others during the genocide. He calls on the international community to summon the same courage to prevent such mass atrocities and genocides from happening again. The President also recognizes Rwanda's progress in rebuilding after the genocide and becoming a leading contributor to peacekeeping missions worldwide. He assures the Rwandan people that the United States will be their partner in pursuing a secure and peaceful future.